    <statement><p>Simplify the function formula, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ K(r) = {\frac{r^{3}-100r}{r^{3}+17r^{2}+70r}} }</m></p>
<p>Reduced <m>K(r)=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{r-10}{r+7}, r\ne -10\hbox{ and }r\ne 0</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cancel common factors.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   K(r) \amp = {\frac{r^{3}-100r}{r^{3}+17r^{2}+70r}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{r\mathopen{}\left(r^{2}-100\right)}}{{r\mathopen{}\left(r^{2}+17r+70\right)}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{r\mathopen{}\left(r+10\right)\mathopen{}\left(r-10\right)}}{{r\mathopen{}\left(r+10\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+7\right)}} \\
                 \amp = {\frac{r-10}{r+7}, r\ne -10\hbox{ and }r\ne 0}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since <m>r(r+10)</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the reduction is <m>r \ne {-10, 0}</m>.</p>
</solution>
